Sentencas: Different cell configurations of anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells (mT-SOFCs) using samaria-doped ceria (SDC) as the electrolyte were fabricated.
Titulo: The effect of anode support on the electrochemical performance of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by gel-casting

Sentencas: Several cells were processed varying the porosity and wall thickness (outer diameter) of NiO-SDC tubular supports.
Titulo: The effect of anode support on the electrochemical performance of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by gel-casting

Sentencas: Suitable aqueous slurry formulations of NiO-SDC for gel-casting were prepared using agarose, as a gelling agent, and sucrose, as a pore former.
Titulo: The effect of anode support on the electrochemical performance of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by gel-casting

Sentencas: The subsequent NiO-SDC anode functional layer (AFL), the SDC electrolyte and the La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 similar to delta-SDC cathode were deposited by spray-coating.
Titulo: The effect of anode support on the electrochemical performance of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by gel-casting

Sentencas: Pre-sintering temperatures of the supports were optimized from linear shrinkage curves, thus obtaining after co-sintering, a dense electrolyte without anode-electrolyte delamination.
Titulo: The effect of anode support on the electrochemical performance of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by gel-casting

Sentencas: Electrochemical characterization of mT-SOFC cells fabricated by agarose gel-casting is reported by the first time.
Titulo: The effect of anode support on the electrochemical performance of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by gel-casting

Sentencas: The cell with a support of 2.6 mm diameter, 380 mm wall thickness, an active area of 1 cm(2) and added porosity, using 10 wt% sucrose, achieved a maximum power density of about 400 mW cm(-2) at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: The effect of anode support on the electrochemical performance of microtubular solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by gel-casting
